div.div: User sets preferences for what type of data trends and data anomalies they want to receive.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 156px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;
div.div: App receives aggregated data from WEB API calls and displays in various data visualizations. App periodically checks the server for any information the user specified they wanted notifications for.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 156px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;
div.div: App visuals will leverage the power BI service to display different types of data visualization. This is in the form of a Web API.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 116px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;
div.div: User changes a configuration setting in the app for a weather station.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 146px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;
div.div: App send a Web API call to the Azure Iot Hub that will trigger an update of that station's configuration settings.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 116px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;
